writing-discipline observations:
  - All 3 pages exceed the 10-FAQ minimum at 12 FAQs each (top of the 10-12 band per
    brief specification).
  - Word counts (body content): C13 ~3,200 body words; C14 ~3,500; C15 ~3,500. All
    within +/-10% of the brief's 2,800-3,400 hub-anchor target band; C14 and C15 sit
    at the heavier end to accommodate the doctrinal-mechanic and four-tax-stack
    depth.
  - LFRA 2024 commencement framing applied per HP §31.3 ("commencement is phased
    through 2026-2027; some Part 2 provisions are commenced, others require secondary
    legislation"; verification responsibility explicitly placed on the reader before
    relying on specific changes).
  - Marriage value framed as ABOLISHED post-LFRA-2024 commencement (not "abolished"
    unconditionally) per HP §31.9 do-not-write discipline.
  - Para 14 of FA 2003 Sch 17A explicitly framed as REPEALED by FA 2013 Sch 41 para
    7(1) on both C14 and C15, with an explicit aside on C14 calling out this as the
    "most-common drift point in older lease-variation commentary".
  - FA 2003 s.43(3)(b) surrender treatment explicitly contradicts the common "no SDLT
    on surrender" misstatement on C15, with an explicit aside calling out the error.
  - FA 2003 s.74 collective enfranchisement per-flat fraction explicitly worked on C13
    with a numerical comparison showing nil SDLT vs ~£63,750 SDLT without s.74 on the
    same aggregate consideration.
  - TCGA 1992 Schedule 8 wasting-asset depreciation explicitly worked on C15 with an
    aside calling out the non-linear depreciation curve as one of the "most
    consistently mishandled" areas of property CGT.
  - IHT s.142 deed-of-variation name-collision explicitly disambiguated in C15 opening
    paragraph plus opening FAQ plus dedicated section, with cross-link to existing
    IHT page.

